# doc/index.md (name_index) Formatting Rules

- keep_sorted              : Keep lexicographic order by name.
- blank_line_on_root_change: Insert blank line when root term
                             changes (first term before `_`).
- fixed_format             : Use `name : type : detail`.
- align_columns            : Align first and second `:` columns
                             vertically.
- short_type               : Keep `type` short and lowercase
                             (`css`, `class`, `id`, `file`, `image`,
                             `domain`, `section`, `field`).
- short_detail             : Keep `detail` short, lowercase, and
                             user-meaningful (avoid "token").
- avoid_repeats            : If `detail` just repeats the name
                             words, replace with a short clarifier.
